        <name>conn_rate_changed</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_conn_cb::conn_rate_changed</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>LE Connection Rate Changed event. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This callback notifies the application that the connection rate parameters (including both connection interval and subrating) of the connection may have changed.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>conn</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Connection object. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>status</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>HCI Status from LE Connection Rate Change event. Possible Status codes:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Success (0x00)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Unknown Connection Identifier (0x02)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Command Disallowed (0x0C)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Unsupported Feature or Parameter Value (0x11)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Invalid HCI Command Parameters (0x12)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Unsupported Remote Feature (0x1A)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Unsupported LL Parameter Value (0x20) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>params</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>New connection rate parameters. The connection rate parameters will be NULL if <computeroutput>status</computeroutput> is not <ref refid="hci__types_8h_1a27c890210eded48f159073cccef8582a" kindref="member">BT_HCI_ERR_SUCCESS</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
